<help osdsearch>

object short description search

This function allows you to search for objects with short descriptions
matching a perl compatible regular expression.


Syntax:  osdsearch 'pattern'

Modifiers: All modifiers should be enclosed in (? ):
(?i) case insensitive matching.
(?m) multi-line matching. (changes meaning of $ anchor to eoln)

Examples:

To find all objects with "sword" or "dagger" in their description.
osdsearch 'sword|dagger'    

To find all objects with a case insensitive match for "sword" followed by
anything followed by "sorrows"
osdsearch '(?i)sword.*sorrows'

<color=red>
See Also:  oldsearch msdsearch mldsearch
</color></help>
